%% rhods-operator Data Flow Diagram
%% Generated by: Claude Opus 4.6
%% Source: architecture/rhoai-2.25/rhods-operator.md

sequenceDiagram
    participant Admin as Admin / User
    participant K8sAPI as Kubernetes API<br/>6443/TCP HTTPS TLS 1.2+
    participant Webhook as Webhook Server<br/>9443/TCP HTTPS TLS
    participant DSCICtrl as DSCI Controller
    participant DSCCtrl as DSC Controller
    participant CompCtrl as Component Controllers
    participant SvcCtrl as Service Controllers<br/>(Auth, Monitoring, ServiceMesh)

    Note over Admin,SvcCtrl: Flow 1: Platform Initialization (DSCI)

    Admin->>K8sAPI: Create DSCInitialization CR<br/>Auth: Bearer Token / Client Cert
    K8sAPI->>Webhook: POST /validate-dscinitialization<br/>HTTPS, API server client cert
    Webhook-->>K8sAPI: Admission Response (Allow/Deny)
    K8sAPI-->>Admin: CR Created
    K8sAPI->>DSCICtrl: Watch event (DSCI created)
    DSCICtrl->>K8sAPI: Create application namespace<br/>ServiceAccount token
    DSCICtrl->>K8sAPI: Deploy network policies<br/>ServiceAccount token
    DSCICtrl->>K8sAPI: Create Auth CR
    K8sAPI->>SvcCtrl: Watch event (Auth CR)
    SvcCtrl->>K8sAPI: Create ClusterRoles, RoleBindings<br/>for admin/allowed groups
    DSCICtrl->>K8sAPI: Create Monitoring CR
    K8sAPI->>SvcCtrl: Watch event (Monitoring CR)
    SvcCtrl->>K8sAPI: Deploy MonitoringStack, Tempo,<br/>OpenTelemetry, ServiceMonitors
    DSCICtrl->>K8sAPI: Create ServiceMesh CR
    K8sAPI->>SvcCtrl: Watch event (ServiceMesh CR)
    SvcCtrl->>K8sAPI: Create SMCP, SMM, Authorino,<br/>AuthConfig resources

    Note over Admin,SvcCtrl: Flow 2: Component Lifecycle Management (DSC)

    Admin->>K8sAPI: Create/Update DataScienceCluster CR<br/>Auth: Bearer Token / Client Cert
    K8sAPI->>Webhook: POST /mutate-datasciencecluster<br/>HTTPS, API server client cert
    Webhook-->>K8sAPI: Mutated CR
    K8sAPI->>Webhook: POST /validate-datasciencecluster<br/>HTTPS, API server client cert
    Webhook-->>K8sAPI: Admission Response (Allow)
    K8sAPI-->>Admin: CR Created/Updated
    K8sAPI->>DSCCtrl: Watch event (DSC created/updated)
    DSCCtrl->>K8sAPI: Create/update component CRs<br/>(Dashboard, KServe, etc.)
    K8sAPI->>CompCtrl: Watch event (component CRs)
    CompCtrl->>K8sAPI: Apply kustomize manifests<br/>(Deployments, Services, CRDs)
    CompCtrl-->>K8sAPI: Component deployed
